trans-unit.source: Specifies the base class for any UI element that appears on the [!INCLUDE[wf2](~/add/includes/wf2-md.md)] designer canvas and that visually represents an instance of an atomic item that can be edited.
trans-unit.target: Angir basisklasse for alle UI-elementet som vises på den [!INCLUDE[wf2](~/add/includes/wf2-md.md)] designer arbeidssonen, og at visuelt representerer en forekomst av et atomic element som kan redigeres.

trans-unit.source: Examples of items represented by a WorkflowViewElement include <xref:System.Activities.Activity> and <xref:System.Activities.Statements.FlowNode>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Activities.Activity>Og <xref:System.Activities.Statements.FlowNode>.</xref:System.Activities.Statements.FlowNode> </xref:System.Activities.Activity> eksempler på elementer som er representert av en WorkflowViewElement

trans-unit.source: `WorkflowViewElement` provides a common contract that the designer uses to render the visual element onto the designer surface and to interact with it through the various editing actions.
trans-unit.target: `WorkflowViewElement`inneholder en vanlig kontrakt designer brukes til å gjengi visual elementet til utformingsoverflaten og samhandle med den via ulike redigeringshandlinger.

trans-unit.source: If you are building a designer for an <xref:System.Activities.Activity>, you should use the <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.ActivityDesigner> base type.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du lager en utformer for en <xref:System.Activities.Activity>, bør du bruke den <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.ActivityDesigner>basistype.</xref:System.Activities.Presentation.ActivityDesigner> </xref:System.Activities.Activity>

trans-unit.source: If there are non-activity elements that need to be treated as first class items on the designer canvas, such as a toolbox item that needs to be draggable throughout the canvas, or for cut-and-paste scenarios, use `WorkflowViewElement` as the base class.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ikke aktiviteten elementer som skal behandles som førsteklasses elementer på designer arbeidssonen, for eksempel et verktøykassen-element som må være firkantete i hele arbeidssonen, eller klipp og Lim scenarioer Bruk `WorkflowViewElement` som basisklassen.

trans-unit.source: If you do not want to use the standard activity chrome for an activity designer, `WorkflowViewElement` should be used as the base type to provide the most flexibility.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du ikke vil bruke standard aktiviteten chrome for en Aktivitetsdesigner `WorkflowViewElement` skal brukes som basistype til å angi størst fleksibilitet.

trans-unit.source: A WorkflowViewElement represents a <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.Model.ModelItem> in the UI and provides code access to the model item and an <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.EditingContext> that allows changes to be made.
trans-unit.target: En WorkflowViewElement representerer en <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.Model.ModelItem>i Brukergrensesnittet og gir kode tilgang til modellelementet og en <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.EditingContext>som tillater endringer gjøres.</xref:System.Activities.Presentation.EditingContext> </xref:System.Activities.Presentation.Model.ModelItem>
